# gen174 — F3 (semantics, call graph): parrot0 attributes each call in a body to
# its enclosing function (code_calls/2), derived from structure. Nested calls in
# an argument list are caught; a function with no calls is reported honestly.
#expect: pass
#faculty: callgraph
> what does main call: int main(void) { greet(); cleanup(); return 0; }
< main calls greet and cleanup
> what does h call: int h(int x) { return f(g(x)); }
< h calls f and g
> what does add call: int add(int a, int b) { return a + b; }
< add does not call any function
